body:
See https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187780-t-compiler.2Fwg-llvm/topic/Calling.20ParseCommandLineOptions.20twice/near/213808524

[`LLVMRustSetLLVMOptions`](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/c71248b70870960af9993de4f31d3cba9bbce7e8/compiler/rustc_llvm/llvm-wrapper/PassWrapper.cpp#L586) currently ignores all attempts to set the LLVM options after the first. It seems that calling [`cl::ResetCommandLineParser`](https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/blob/225065b9a8e7ec0479b6ee8334f8fe4d4118f875/llvm/lib/Support/CommandLine.cpp#L2599) first is enough to support reconfiguring the LLVM options.

@rustbot modify labels: +A-llvm +C-enhancement
